    slug: "subah-shaam-allah-kai-naam-azkar-card",
    description: `Subah Shaam Allah Kai Naam (Azkar Card) is a physical morning and evening supplication card printed with the remembrances of Allah that Muslims are encouraged to recite at the beginning and end of each day. This card serves as a portable, durable reference that helps believers maintain the practice of daily azkar (remembrances) by providing the exact text of the recommended supplications in an easy-to-read format. The practice of reciting morning and evening azkar is well-established in the Sunnah of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), who taught his companions specific supplications for protection, blessings, and spiritual renewal at these two important times of day.

The card contains the Arabic text of each supplication along with transliteration for those who are still learning to read Arabic script, and an Urdu translation that conveys the meaning of each dhikr. This three-layer presentation — Arabic, transliteration, and translation — makes the card accessible to a wide audience, from children who are just beginning their Islamic education to adults who want to deepen their practice of daily remembrance. The supplications include the morning and evening versions of Ayat al-Kursi, the three Quls (Surah Al-Ikhlas, Al-Falaq, and An-Nas), specific tasbih and tahmid formulas taught by the Prophet, and various duas for protection from harm, blessings in daily affairs, and forgiveness of sins.

The physical construction of the card is designed for daily use and long-term durability. It is printed on thick, laminated card stock that resists tearing, water damage, and the general wear and tear of being handled every morning and evening. The compact size allows it to fit easily into a wallet, purse, pocket, or prayer mat bag, making it convenient to carry wherever one goes. The clear typography and organized layout ensure that each supplication is easy to find and read, even in low-light conditions or when the reader is in a hurry. This azkar card is particularly useful for travelers, students, and busy professionals who may not have access to a full prayer book during their daily routine. It also serves as an excellent tool for teaching children the habit of morning and evening remembrance, as the concise format is less overwhelming than a full-length dua book.`,
